<subSubSection pageNumber="739" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="739">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="739">Note:</emphasis>
Wherry (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="739">Genus</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polemoniaceae" genus="Phlox" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Phlox</taxonomicName>
: 100. 1955) treated the Plukenet element as the type, but the voucher collection was subsequently shown to belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Walt.) Steud." authorityName="Steud." baseAuthorityName="Walt." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Ruellia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caroliniensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="739">Ruellia caroliniensis</emphasis>
(Walt.) Steud.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Acanthaceae</taxonomicName>
). Wilbur (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="739">Taxon</emphasis>
36: 131. 1987) rejected this choice on the grounds that the plate conflicted with the generic description, and chose 217.10 (LINN) as 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
in its place. Reveal, however, believed 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Wherry’s">Wherry's</normalizedToken>
choice to be valid and proposed (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="739">Taxon</emphasis>
38: 515. 1989) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polemoniaceae" genus="Phlox" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ovata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="739">P. ovata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for conservation with a conserved type. After a further response from Wilbur (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="739">l.c.</emphasis>
39: 297-298. 1990), the Committee for Spermatophyta ruled (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="739">l.c.</emphasis>
42: 694. 1993) that 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Wherry’s">Wherry's</normalizedToken>
choice should be superseded, that 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Wilbur’s">Wilbur's</normalizedToken>
choice was valid, and that the proposal was therefore unnecessary, and not recommended.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
